This paper deals with the computation of distances between persistence modules, which is a central task in topological data analysis. The paper specifically focuses on $n$-parameter interval decomposable modules, which are a reasonably complicated class of persistence modules. This topic is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG), as well as data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents algorithms for computing these distances, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the applications of these distances in topological data analysis, which is a subfield of scientific computing (cs.SI).
